About Us







Always On since 1864.

CONSOL Energy, a publicly-owned Pittsburgh-based energy producer, is one of the largest independent natural gas exploration, development and production companies, with operations centered in the major shale formations of the Appalachian basin. Since our founding in 1860 and our first active operations in 1864, CONSOL has been a pioneer in providing affordable, abundant, reliable domestic energy. A century and a half on from our founding, CONSOL's employees continue to be at the forefront of generating the fuels that power the nation. As we like to say, America’s energy truly does start here.
But we do more than just follow the roadmap to America’s energy future – we are shaping that map every day through our innovative approach to responsible energy production. Our energy continues to support American life 24/7/365 by creating family-and community-sustaining jobs, as well as keeping our nation competitive in the global marketplace.
Our strong record on safety and environmental stewardship, as well as our commitment to the communities where we have lived and worked for generations, has helped enable us to become the dynamic and accomplished energy company we are today. In fact, our core values – Safety, Compliance and Continuous Improvement – are the foundational elements of our business model and distinguish us from our peers.
The journey began over 150 years ago and continues today. CONSOL Energy strives each and every day to maintain its position as an innovator and one of the safest and most respected energy producers in the world.





